      &#12298;thinking in Java&#12299;&#20013;&#65292;<font face="Georgia">This is what all classes that <i>implement</i>&#160;this particular interface will look like.&#8221; Thus, any code that uses a particular <b>interface</b>&#160;knows what methods might be called for that <b>interface</b>, and that&#8217;s all. So the <b>interface</b>&#160;is used to establish a &#8220;protocol&#8221; between classes.</font>
